{
  "texts": [
    "The input for the method is a partially completed ontology term (for example, just the term label, such as \"hydroxyprolinuria\"), and the output is a JSON or YAML object that has all desired fields populated, including the text definition, logical definition, and relationships.The procedure is shown in Fig. 1.",
    "As an initial step, each ontology term and any additional contextual information is translated into a vector embedding, which is used as an index for retrieving relevant terms.",
    "Additional contextual information can include the contents of a GitHub issue tracker, which might contain text or semistructured information of relevance to the request.",
    "The main ontology completion step works by first constructing a prompt using relevant contextual information.",
    "The prompt is passed as an input to an LLM, and the results are parsed to retrieve the completed term object."
  ]
}